name: Kevin “KC”
text:
Loaded up pretty quick. It's very dirty. Your truck will need a wash afterwards. Also take your shoes off before getting back into your truck.
Be sure to have safety vest and vest or you will not be allowed in. There is a home depot up the street. Walmart also but they don't have any. Overnight parking is permitted

name: HAYDER AL ROBAY
text: Nice people in the shipping office as well as security guard, overnight parking & driver’s restroom, 2 hrs loading time! Only the place is messy you might need to wash your truck & trailer after

name: B GILL
text: Loading time not to bad.  Heavy loads. Scale on site. Need to wash your truck after leaving this place.

name: Zet D
text: My first time going here I guess after a rainy day and boy was I in for it! Dispatch didn't tell me I needed a hardhat and you have to park in a staging area then walk half a mile to shipping office. Got to my door got loaded in about 30 mins!!

name: Joseph Jette
text:
As a trucker, it is important to have use of a scale that is accurate. Theirs is not! Under estimated my gross by 550 lbs.
Day time crew were easy to get along with at shipper office, but night crew just seemed somewhat irritated at life.

name: Ness Jett
text: Always leave place with a dirty floor and white shoes instead of black.  But cool views.

name: Jay Dixon
text: Truckers. place is awesome. yes bumpy roads so forth on its a quarry (what do you expect!) Once I got checked in an got my door that was that. Loaded me in 30 minutes. Went back to office got my paperwork an was gone. All together time almost 2 hours not bad. Vest all times hard hat included unless in your truck.

name: MR. DARCY DuVALL
text: Rivers made of marble!

name: Tiger Maakhari
text: Very very fast loaded no appointment frist come frist service nice poeple 30 mnt loaded

name: Muhammad AlOmar
text: Worse ever,  been waiting for 8hours and not loaded yet , very bad attitude from one of the guys there his name Jaick or jack total trash works at night, he should be fired ASAP , he makes this company looks very bad...

name: Larry Smith
text: Folks are nice. Not a bad place to load freight. Being a quarry it is dusty when dry and a mess when it's raining.

name: Eunice Bluster
text: My fiancé works here. From what I can tell it is a okay place to get the materials you need as far as gravel and stuff like that..they grid the marble down to almost nothing but dust..so I will advise you not to drive your freshly washed car on the property🚗💨 smh I have to stay at the carwash on 280😘 hint???
